reviewText: This might have been the single worst course I have ever taken in 25 years of learning. The videos contain no  actionable information, the resources are broken half the time, or irrelevant, or just plain useless. The quizes are terribly designed and don't really test knowledge of the subject. Seriously, anybody consider doing this course should just not.
a very bad bad bad bad course to learn

Dont spend money here. No assistance from professor. Quiz are very difficult since no sufficient videos.
Bad Course.

There is interesting material in this course, but the overall experience is frustrating to the point of being net negative.  Quiz questions cover material which has not been presented yet or covered in the "web tours".  Some answers scored as correct (or wrong) contradict the "web tour" material, maybe due to poor QA of the multiple answers and double negatives in the choices.  The course also says you must obtain a book for the final quiz which, it turns out, is unnecessary.

S​ome good information, but lecture videos don't contain any useful informaion, mostly just previews of what is on the 'web tour'  most of the learning is done via wikipeia articles.  A lot of the links  to webpages are dead or require logins.    Quiz questions use vauge language so it's difficult to know if you are picking the correct answer.  Some of the quiz questins are preseseted before the material is covered.

This was a relatively hard course for me. Its courses were great but required extensive reading of the material. I had a huge familiarity with the things I were learning but I have a hard time imagining people without any background going through all of this. Althought the test questions weren't hard, they were also challenging at sometimes. Some of the reading material links were also expired. I did have a great time with this course but still see that it could be improved.
